<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="107" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,680]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,511,536]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[324,489,513,536]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acuminatus">
<emphasis box="[324,489,513,536]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">H. acuminatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Knight" authorityName="Knight" box="[620,821,511,536]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alstoni">
<emphasis box="[620,733,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">H. alstoni</emphasis>
Knight
</taxonomicName>
from Celebes and 
<taxonomicName authority="Knight" authorityName="Knight" box="[1041,1250,511,536]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="festivus">
<emphasis box="[1041,1162,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">H. festivus</emphasis>
Knight
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry name="Christmas Island" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">Christmas Island</collectingCountry>
, in that each aedeagal shaft terminates in a filamentous process. However, the three species differ in the shape of the shaft: in 
<taxonomicName box="[404,570,585,608]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acuminatus">
<emphasis box="[404,570,585,608]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">H. acuminatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the shaft slightly widens distally before the gonopore and in the other two species it is of uniform width and widens abruptly either mesally (in 
<taxonomicName box="[931,1042,620,645]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alstoni">
<emphasis box="[931,1042,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">H. alstoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or laterally (in 
<taxonomicName box="[1228,1347,620,644]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="festivus">
<emphasis box="[1228,1347,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">H. festivus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) before attaining the gonopore.
</paragraph>
